section.section:
"Class of business" means:
cash loans made by banks and not secured by real estate;
cash loans made by banks and secured by real estate;
cash loans made by credit unions;
cash loans made by creditors other than banks and credit unions and not secured by real estate;
cash loans made by creditors other than banks and secured by real estate;
production credit association and other agricultural loans;
installment sales finance contracts; or
open end credit, including revolving charge agreements and credit card accounts.
